---
import Base from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';
const title = 'Cascade Simulator';
const subtitle = 'Click launch. Watch a campaign multiply itself.';
---
<Base title={title} description={subtitle}>
  <article class="etude-page">
    <header class="etude-head">
      <p class="etude-kicker">Etude · Campaign Cascade</p>
      <h1 class="etude-title">{title}</h1>
      <p class="etude-relief">{subtitle}</p>
      <nav class="etude-nav">
        <a href="/etudes/campaign-cascade/">← campaign cascade etudes</a>
        <span class="etude-nav-sep">·</span>
        <a href="/essays/the-campaign-cascade/">essay</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <section class="etude-intro">
      <p>The claim from <em>The Loop</em>: a cross-cutting initiative — a mass-PR migration, say — does not stall quietly. It multiplies. The original campaign stalls. Escalation triggers a new campaign. That one stalls too. The new campaign is rational. So is the next. None of them complete the original work.</p>
      <p>Press launch. Watch four campaigns spawn in sequence. Each is rational. Each is the right idea. The original migration creeps forward at a glacial pace.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="etude-stage">
      <div class="etude-card">
        <p class="etude-step">Simulator</p>
        <div class="controls">
          <button type="button" id="launch" class="etude-next launch-btn">Launch campaign</button>
          <button type="button" id="reset" class="etude-ghost reset-btn" disabled>Reset</button>
        </div>

        <div class="stage" id="stage">
          <div class="campaigns" id="campaigns"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="stats" id="stats">
          <div class="stat"><span class="stat-label">Campaigns launched</span><span class="stat-value" id="stat-campaigns">0</span></div>
          <div class="stat"><span class="stat-label">PRs created</span><span class="stat-value" id="stat-prs">0</span></div>
          <div class="stat"><span class="stat-label">PRs merged</span><span class="stat-value" id="stat-merged">0</span></div>
          <div class="stat"><span class="stat-label">Original migration completion</span><span class="stat-value" id="stat-completion">0%</span></div>
          <div class="stat"><span class="stat-label">Wall time</span><span class="stat-value" id="stat-time">0 weeks</span></div>
          <div class="stat"><span class="stat-label">Effort</span><span class="stat-value" id="stat-effort">0 person-weeks</span></div>
        </div>

        <div id="banner" class="banner" aria-live="polite"></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="etude-failure">
      <h2 class="etude-failure-title">The failure mode</h2>
      <p>This is the failure mode. Each campaign is rational — escalation, tracking, dashboarding, decommissioning are all the right idea. The system can still fail because the right ideas multiply faster than they finish. The dead zone is where you can identify every part of the cascade and still can't stop it.</p>
    </section>

    <footer class="etude-coda">
      <p>Welcome to the cascade.</p>
    </footer>
  </article>
</Base>

<script is:inline>
  const CAMPAIGNS = [
    { id: 1, label: 'Campaign 1: migrate to Java 21' },
    { id: 2, label: 'Campaign 2: escalation framework — track campaign completion at PMR' },
    { id: 3, label: 'Campaign 3: dashboarding for escalation tracking' },
    { id: 4, label: 'Campaign 4: process to decommission unused dashboards' },
  ];

  const DOTS_PER_CAMPAIGN = 30;
  const FAN_OUT_MS = 600;
  const SETTLE_MS = 2400;
  const BETWEEN_MS = 600;

  let running = false;
  let totals = { campaigns: 0, prs: 0, merged: 0 };

  function pickColor() {
    const r = Math.random();
    if (r < 0.30) return 'green';
    if (r < 0.80) return 'yellow';
    return 'red';
  }

  function tickTo(el, target, suffix = '', ms = 800) {
    const start = parseInt(el.dataset.cur || '0', 10);
    const t0 = performance.now();
    function step(now) {
      const k = Math.min(1, (now - t0) / ms);
      const eased = 1 - Math.pow(1 - k, 3);
      const cur = Math.round(start + (target - start) * eased);
      el.textContent = cur + suffix;
      el.dataset.cur = String(cur);
      if (k < 1) requestAnimationFrame(step);
      else {
        el.textContent = target + suffix;
        el.dataset.cur = String(target);
      }
    }
    requestAnimationFrame(step);
  }

  function setText(el, text) { el.textContent = text; }

  function buildCampaign(c) {
    const wrap = document.createElement('div');
    wrap.className = 'campaign';
    wrap.dataset.id = String(c.id);

    const box = document.createElement('div');
    box.className = 'campaign-box';
    box.textContent = c.label;
    wrap.appendChild(box);

    const grid = document.createElement('div');
    grid.className = 'dot-grid';
    for (let i = 0; i < DOTS_PER_CAMPAIGN; i++) {
      const dot = document.createElement('div');
      dot.className = 'dot';
      dot.style.setProperty('--i', String(i));
      grid.appendChild(dot);
    }
    wrap.appendChild(grid);

    const summary = document.createElement('div');
    summary.className = 'campaign-summary';
    wrap.appendChild(summary);

    return wrap;
  }

  function settleDots(wrap) {
    return new Promise((resolve) => {
      const dots = wrap.querySelectorAll('.dot');
      const counts = { green: 0, yellow: 0, red: 0 };
      dots.forEach((dot, idx) => {
        const delay = 200 + idx * 60 + Math.random() * 200;
        setTimeout(() => {
          const color = pickColor();
          counts[color]++;
          dot.classList.add('settled', color);
          totals.prs += 1;
          if (color === 'green') totals.merged += 1;
          updateLiveStats();
        }, delay);
      });

      setTimeout(() => {
        const summary = wrap.querySelector('.campaign-summary');
        summary.innerHTML =
          `<span class="chip chip-green">${counts.green} merged</span>` +
          `<span class="chip chip-yellow">${counts.yellow} stalled</span>` +
          `<span class="chip chip-red">${counts.red} rejected</span>`;
        resolve(counts);
      }, 200 + DOTS_PER_CAMPAIGN * 60 + 400);
    });
  }

  function updateLiveStats() {
    const cEl = document.getElementById('stat-campaigns');
    const pEl = document.getElementById('stat-prs');
    const mEl = document.getElementById('stat-merged');
    cEl.textContent = String(totals.campaigns);
    pEl.textContent = String(totals.prs);
    const pct = totals.prs > 0 ? Math.round((totals.merged / totals.prs) * 100) : 0;
    mEl.textContent = `${totals.merged} (${pct}%)`;
  }

  async function runCascade() {
    if (running) return;
    running = true;
    document.getElementById('launch').disabled = true;
    document.getElementById('reset').disabled = true;
    document.getElementById('banner').innerHTML = '';
    document.getElementById('banner').className = 'banner';

    const host = document.getElementById('campaigns');
    host.innerHTML = '';
    totals = { campaigns: 0, prs: 0, merged: 0 };
    updateLiveStats();
    setText(document.getElementById('stat-completion'), '0%');
    setText(document.getElementById('stat-time'), '0 weeks');
    setText(document.getElementById('stat-effort'), '0 person-weeks');

    for (let i = 0; i < CAMPAIGNS.length; i++) {
      const wrap = buildCampaign(CAMPAIGNS[i]);
      host.appendChild(wrap);
      // animate fan-in
      requestAnimationFrame(() => {
        wrap.classList.add('visible');
        wrap.querySelectorAll('.dot').forEach(d => d.classList.add('fanned'));
      });

      totals.campaigns += 1;
      updateLiveStats();

      await settleDots(wrap);
      await sleep(BETWEEN_MS);
    }

    // final stat reveal
    tickTo(document.getElementById('stat-completion'), 27, '%', 1200);
    tickTo(document.getElementById('stat-time'), 3, ' weeks', 1200);
    tickTo(document.getElementById('stat-effort'), 14, ' person-weeks', 1400);

    await sleep(900);

    const banner = document.getElementById('banner');
    banner.className = 'banner banner-shown';
    banner.innerHTML =
      '<strong>The original migration is 27% complete.</strong> ' +
      'Three other campaigns spawned to track completion. ' +
      'None of them complete the migration. ' +
      '<em>Welcome to the cascade.</em>';

    document.getElementById('reset').disabled = false;
    running = false;
  }

  function sleep(ms) { return new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, ms)); }

  document.getElementById('launch').addEventListener('click', () => {
    runCascade();
  });
  document.getElementById('reset').addEventListener('click', () => {
    if (running) return;
    document.getElementById('campaigns').innerHTML = '';
    totals = { campaigns: 0, prs: 0, merged: 0 };
    updateLiveStats();
    setText(document.getElementById('stat-completion'), '0%');
    setText(document.getElementById('stat-time'), '0 weeks');
    setText(document.getElementById('stat-effort'), '0 person-weeks');
    document.getElementById('banner').innerHTML = '';
    document.getElementById('banner').className = 'banner';
    document.getElementById('launch').disabled = false;
  });
</script>

<style is:global>
  /* === etude page chrome === */
  .etude-page {
    max-width: 38rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .etude-head {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .etude-kicker {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: var(--label-size);
    letter-spacing: var(--label-tracking);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
  }
  .etude-title {
    font-family: var(--serif-display);
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .etude-relief {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
  }
  .etude-nav {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .etude-nav a { color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; }
  .etude-nav a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
  .etude-nav-sep { margin: 0 0.5rem; opacity: 0.5; }

  .etude-intro {
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .etude-intro p {
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .etude-stage {
    min-height: 22rem;
  }

  /* === card === */
  .etude-card {
    background: var(--bg-soft);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.5rem 1.25rem;
  }
  .etude-step {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: var(--label-size);
    letter-spacing: var(--label-tracking);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
  }

  /* === controls === */
  .controls {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  /* primary button (launch) — uses etude-next pattern */
  .etude-next {
    appearance: none;
    -webkit-appearance: none;
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    padding: 0.65rem 1.2rem;
    border: none;
    background: var(--text);
    color: var(--bg);
    border-radius: 999px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background 180ms ease, transform 120ms ease, opacity 180ms ease;
    min-height: 44px;
  }
  .etude-next:hover:not(:disabled) {
    background: var(--accent);
  }
  .etude-next:active:not(:disabled) {
    transform: scale(0.97);
  }
  .etude-next:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--accent);
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .etude-next:disabled {
    opacity: 0.4;
    cursor: not-allowed;
  }
  .launch-btn::after { content: ' →'; }

  /* secondary button (reset) — outlined */
  .etude-ghost {
    appearance: none;
    -webkit-appearance: none;
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    padding: 0.65rem 1.2rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--text);
    border-radius: 999px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: border-color 180ms ease, background 180ms ease, transform 120ms ease, opacity 180ms ease;
    min-height: 44px;
  }
  .etude-ghost:hover:not(:disabled) {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .etude-ghost:active:not(:disabled) {
    transform: scale(0.97);
  }
  .etude-ghost:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--accent);
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .etude-ghost:disabled {
    opacity: 0.4;
    cursor: not-allowed;
  }

  /* === simulation stage === */
  .stage { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; min-height: 4rem; }
  .campaigns { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; }
  .campaign {
    opacity: 0; transform: translateY(8px);
    transition: opacity 280ms ease, transform 280ms ease;
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem 1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: var(--bg);
  }
  .campaign.visible { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  .campaign-box {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.92rem; margin-bottom: 0.6rem; color: var(--text);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent); padding-left: 0.6rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }
  .dot-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(15, 1fr); gap: 6px; padding: 0.4rem 0; }
  .dot {
    width: 14px; height: 14px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--line);
    transform: scale(0.2); opacity: 0;
    transition: transform 420ms cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1), opacity 280ms ease, background 240ms ease, box-shadow 240ms ease;
    transition-delay: calc(var(--i) * 18ms);
  }
  .dot.fanned { transform: scale(1); opacity: 1; }
  .dot.settled.green { background: #3f9650; box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px rgba(63,150,80,0.18); }
  .dot.settled.yellow { background: #d6a52b; box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px rgba(214,165,43,0.18); }
  .dot.settled.red { background: #b8413a; box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px rgba(184,65,58,0.18); }
  .campaign-summary {
    margin-top: 0.6rem; display: flex; gap: 0.4rem; flex-wrap: wrap;
    min-height: 1.4rem; font-family: var(--sans); font-size: 0.78rem;
  }
  .chip {
    padding: 0.15rem 0.55rem; border-radius: 999px;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; font-weight: 600;
  }
  .chip-green { background: rgba(63,150,80,0.14); color: #2c6b39; }
  .chip-yellow { background: rgba(214,165,43,0.18); color: #8a6710; }
  .chip-red { background: rgba(184,65,58,0.14); color: #842c27; }

  /* === stats === */
  .stats {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 0.5rem 1.25rem;
    margin: 1.25rem 0 0; padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 10px; background: var(--bg);
  }
  .stat {
    display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline;
    font-size: 0.9rem; gap: 0.5rem;
  }
  .stat-label { color: var(--muted); font-family: var(--sans); }
  .stat-value {
    font-family: 'Menlo', monospace; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
    font-weight: 600; color: var(--text);
  }

  /* === banner === */
  .banner {
    margin: 1.1rem 0 0; min-height: 0;
    opacity: 0; transform: translateY(6px);
    transition: opacity 380ms ease, transform 380ms ease;
  }
  .banner.banner-shown {
    opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0);
    padding: 1rem 1.15rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    background: rgba(138, 52, 32, 0.06);
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-size: 0.98rem; line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .banner em { color: var(--accent); font-style: italic; }

  /* === failure-mode section === */
  .etude-failure {
    margin: 2.5rem 0 0;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .etude-failure-title {
    font-family: var(--serif-display);
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    line-height: 1.25;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .etude-failure p {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  /* === coda === */
  .etude-coda {
    margin: 2rem 0 0;
    padding-top: 1.25rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .etude-coda p {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* === mobile === */
  @media (max-width: 32rem) {
    .etude-title { font-size: 1.85rem; }
    .etude-card { padding: 1.15rem 1.1rem 1rem; border-radius: 10px; }
    .controls { gap: 0.5rem; }
    .etude-next, .etude-ghost { width: 100%; }
    .stats { grid-template-columns: 1fr; padding: 0.85rem 1rem; }
    .dot-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(10, 1fr); }
    .etude-failure-title { font-size: 1.2rem; }
  }
</style>
</content>
</invoke>